{"type":"message","id":"912991d0","parentId":"ee1d9bc1","timestamp":"2026-05-08T07:07:29.750Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze:\n\n**Current config:**\n- `agents.list`: 2 agents\n  - `main` (id: \"main\", name: \"KITT-AGI\") — no workspace specified, so it uses default\n  - `tts` (id: \"tts\", name: \"TK 选品大师\", workspace: \"e-commerce/sourcing\")\n- `bindings`: routes feishu account \"kiit\" → agent \"main\", account \"tts\" → agent \"tts\"\n\n**Current workspace situation:**\n- `main` agent uses default workspace, which is `~/.openclaw/workspace/`\n\n\n- `tts` agent uses `e-commerce/sourcing` which resolves to `~/.openclaw/workspace/e-commerce/sourcing`\n\n**The proposed structure:**\n```\n~/.openclaw/\n├── openclaw.json\n├── skills/          # global shared skills\n├── workspace-lead/   # main agent (大总管)\n├── workspace-tts/    # tts agent (TK 选品大师)\n├── workspace-geo/     # future\n├── workspace-reddit/  # future\n└── workspace-tiktok/   # future\n```\n\n**What needs to change:**\n1. Create new workspace directories for each agent\n2. Update agent configurations to point to the correct workspace paths\n3. Migrate any existing data from the old workspace locations\n\nNow I'm checking the current workspace structure and what agents are already configured. The main agent doesn't have a workspace explicitly set, so it's using the default, while the tts agent is already pointing to a specific workspace. I should map out the current file locations and then show HALEI what the new configuration would look like.\n","thinkingSignature":"179ab531b351530ce21b4d80b1a4a72a51c9c8b2a5710a1c964e1f3baf385cf9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bztui4ll0qb5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/ && echo \"---\" && ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/e-commerce/ 2>/dev/null && echo \"---\" && ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages"